article.headline: Rider 68, Iona 54
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. -- Ryan Thompson scored 18 points, Harris Mansell had 16 and Rider hit a season-high 13 3-pointers in a 68-54 victory over Iona on Thursday. Mike Ringgold and Novar Gadson added 10 points apiece for the Broncs (7-5, 2-0 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), who were two shy of the school record for 3-pointers in a game. Gary Springer scored 13 points and Milan Prodanovic had 12 for the Gaels (5-9, 0-3), losers in four of their last five. Thompson and Mansell each hit four 3-pointers as Rider made 13 of 27 from behind the arc. The Broncs set the school record of 15 3-pointers last season against Canisius. Prodanovic had four 3-pointers and Jermel Jenkins two as Iona made 8 of 21 from long range. Thompson's 13 first-half points helped Rider take a 34-28 lead at the break. Iona got baskets from Alejo Rodriguez and Scott Machado to get within 50-42 with 11:56 left but could get no closer.
